        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 3:24AM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 323 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Walker, or near Grand Rapids, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Grand Rapids and Walker around 330 AM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Grattan, Belmont,
Murray Lake, Comstock Park, Cannonsburg, Ada, and Northview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
